            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " of a simple, straightforward, and elegant solution: Force big banks to accept some losses and write down the amounts homeowners owed on their mortgages, thereby avoiding mass foreclosures. Soon after winning office, Obama abandoned the pledge to the delight of his Wall Street donors.",
